System Requirements
---------------------------------------

1. JDK (openJDK or Sun Java)
2. Graphwiz
3. GNU/Linux

INPUT FORMAT
---------------------------------------
<set of all states S delimited with a space> 
<set of all input alphabets delimited with a space>
<start state>
<set of end states delimited with a space>
<list of transitions of the form  <state>*<alphabet>=<next_state> >

**For an example check input.txt in current directory

STEPS TO RUN
1. First compile the source files
	$ javac FiniteStateMachine.java
	$ javac GraphViz.java
2. If both compile  successfully, run
	$ java FiniteStateMachine --filename <input_file>
3. By default, if you have evince reader, the gif file 
   should pop up instantly, else edit the code and 
   remove the System command being executed.

